description:
Follow-up from code review on PR for beadle-0he. TestFormatMessages_* in internal/mcp/format_test.go covers known/unknown/bare/long/empty-list/count cases but does not specifically pin the behavior for a message with From header = empty string.

splitSender("") returns (name="", addr=""). formatMessages renders both FROM and EMAIL columns blank for that row. This is the correct behavior (nothing to show) but is not exercised by any current test, so a regression could slip through.

Proposed test:

func TestFormatMessages_EmptyFrom(t *testing.T) {
    when := time.Date(2026, 4, 7, 12, 0, 0, 0, time.UTC)
    msgs := []channel.MessageSummary{{
        ID:         "99",
        From:       "",
        Date:       when,
        Subject:    "hello",
        TrustLevel: channel.Unverified,
    }}
    got := formatMessages(msgs, 1)
    assert.Contains(t, got, "99", "row should render without panic")
    assert.Contains(t, got, "hello", "subject should render")
    // No assertion on FROM/EMAIL content — just that rendering does not panic.
}

Filed during review of PR for beadle-0he. Reviewer flagged as nice-to-have, not blocking. Can fold into the next beadle-formatted PR or take as a standalone 1-file change.
